initial steps
	-------------
	1. download and install git
	2. create a project in pycharm (eg: project1)
	3. Sign in to github and create an empty repository in github with
	 the same name as your project or different name .
	next steps
	----------
	git --version -> checks if the git is installed properly
	git init -> create an empty git repository
	configuring user name and mail to git
	---------------------------------------
	git config --global user.name "username"
	git config --global user.email "email_id"
	git config --list -> check the configuration
	git commands
	-------------
	1. git status -> to get the current status of the project
	2. git add filename.py -> add the file to staging area making it a tracked file
	 git add file1 file2 file3 -> adds multiple files
	 adds all the untracked files to staging area
	 git add *
	 git add .
	3. git rm --cached filename -> unstages/ removes the file from staging area(works only if the file is newly added)
	 git restore --staged filename
	4. git rm --cached -r foldername -> unstages/ removes the entire folder from staging area
	ignoring a file/folder from being visible in untracked area -> create a file named .gitignore
	5. git commit -m "message" -> commits the files to local repository
	6. git log -> detailed information about the commits
	 git log --oneline
	7. git remote add variable_name(origin) url -> giving url some other name
	(If you are being redirected to github authorize page, then click on
	authorize and the rest will be same as here)
	8. git push variable_name(origin) branch(master)
